In terms of profit and employment, the Indian economy’s healthcare sector has emerged as one of the most significant sectors. The Indian healthcare sector is experiencing rapid growth due to improved coverage, expanded functionalities and services and increased public and private spending. Due to which the life expectancy has increased dramatically. As the population of individuals rises in many societies, the number of people affected by chronic diseases, such as diabetes, cardiovascular disease, obesity, and so on, rises as well. As a result, Internet of Things (IoT)-based personalised healthcare is becoming a more significant idea.. This paper’s main goal is to illustrate a cardiac patient e-health data acquisition, transfer, and monitoring system. The smart health monitoring system prototype uses a wireless sensor network to measure various health data, which are then sent to the concerned individual through GPRS. These parameters are also saved in Amazon cloud services for future use.